    {
      "id": "PopularPost94283",
      "post_content": "This worked really well in my poorly built haste/burn deck. First turn, I played a haste 1/1 creature and attacked. Second turn, I played quest for pure flame and another 1/1 creature (attacked). Third turn, I played lightning bolt and another 1/1 creature (attacked as well). Luckily, my opponent didn't want to block with his mana ramp creatures. So I had all three creatures to sacrifice to get an 8/8 on turn 4 that can deal double damage because of quest for pure flame.  \nDevour 1 doesn't make any sense to me though (2 seems alright if you have a bunch of 1/1s). ",
      "posted_by": "Sswift",
